cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.WEB, cs.CR, cs.HC 

This paper is about collecting archived web pages from public web archives, which involves web crawling, information retrieval, and web archiving. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.WEB (Web Technologies). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and limitations of web archiving, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
